

STEP 1:
	edit the file /usr/share/vim/vimXX/filetype.vim,
	or ~/share/vim/vimXX/filetype.vim, if u have no root privilege when installing VIM:
	(XX -- VIM version number, if u use VIM 7.2, namely XX == 72)
	add "au BufNewFile,BufRead *.cflow setf cflow",
	between "augroup filetypedetect" and "augroup END";
	
STEP 2:
	move cflow.vim to /usr/share/vim/vimXX/filetype.vim,
	or ~/share/vim/vimXX/filetype.vim, same reason.


NOTICE:
	Regard cflow's output as a new language, so the file name suffix should be ".cflow"
	Just like "cflow -o xxx.cflow"
	
SNAPSHOT:
	cyan	--	functions defined myself
	red	--	system functions
	purple	--	variables
	orange	--	number
	yellow	--	file name
	green	--	type keywords in C
	white	--	something else
	

Enjoy it
